reviews.text: Small local shopping centre; choices are limited
there are plenty trading card game shops, if you are a fan of card game, you should come here to have alook
Look for cards and figures? There's plenty! You will find a few shops selling antiques as well
The address is wrong, waste of time.

you can find Chinese restaurant at upper floor. mainly serving senior group. 
comparatively the plaza design is quite old. elevator available for going up, you need to walk when going downstairs.

reviews.text: 👍打完拳後去☕飲茶👏
○K

香港集玩卡牌遊戲的集中地，有不少同類型的店家。能找到不同TCG的商品，及有機會跟其他玩家對戰。
商場環境較為老化，偶有滴水或中央空調失靈的情況。商場大約每天晚上10點左右關閉中央空調，環境會較為悶熱。

商場的結構，尤如“8”字的鏡射設計，初次到來的人，會比較容易迷失方向。
於商場1樓，分別設有1條通往商場2樓的扶手電梯，以及另一條通往酒樓的扶手電梯。（※附上商場地圖，及2條扶手電梯的照片供參考用）
附帶一提，下樓只有樓梯可以用。

reviews.text: This place has some really great food! The dishes are well seasoned and comes out hot so you know they are made to order. The price is decent for what you get as well.

Amazing Thai food! We ordered their Red Curry and the Jumbo Chilli Prawns. Their menu makes it easy to find recommended dishes, so A+ for that.

Reasonably priced with good portions. Staff were friendly and helpful. 

Note we had to wait before getting a table.
Decent food at reasonable prices. The soft-shelled crab in curry sauce was quite tasty, but the prawn cakes were a little rubbery. Would try the fish cakes next time.

Almost authentic, and great value for your money. You can taste the freshness in their ingredients and the delicate aroma of the spices they use. How often do you find large, crisp shrimps in fried rice? The flavor, however, is a little on the bland side to my liking. My favorite dishes are boneless Hainanese chicken, shrimp Pad Thai, and pineapple fried rice.
reasonable price, the pad thai could have added in more flavour!
